         <div type="commentary">
            <p>l. 1, The honorand is probably Apollonios Papias  <ref type="iAph" target="">1335</ref> (=64.235), perhaps the brother of the donor in <ref type="iAph" target="">1257</ref> (=MAMA 449, under Domitian) and of the honorand in <ref type="iAph" target="">1765</ref> (=CIG 2766). The restoration of the statues, which is apparently referred to again in <ref type="iAph" target="">564</ref>, was perhaps after the Trajanic earthquake. The same group apparently reappears in an inscription at Plarasa (Paton), where Secundus has become P. Aelius Secundus.</p>
            <p>The singular verb with the plural subject is common in these texts.</p>
